#: templates/FAQ.html:7
msgid "High School English Paper Club"
msgstr ""

#: templates/FAQ.html:123
msgid ""
"Q. I missed the registration deadline. May I still register or submit an "
"essay?"
msgstr ""

#: templates/FAQ.html:124
msgid ""
"A. No. Only candidates who registered before 31 May will be able to "
"submit an essay."
msgstr ""

#: templates/FAQ.html:129
msgid ""
"Q. Are footnotes, endnotes, a bibliography or references counted towards "
"the word\n"
"        limit?"
msgstr ""

#: templates/FAQ.html:131
msgid "A. No. Only the body of the essay is counted."
msgstr ""

#: templates/FAQ.html:135
msgid "Q. Are in-text citations counted towards the word limit?"
msgstr ""

#: templates/FAQ.html:136
msgid ""
"A. If you are using an in-text based referencing format, such as APA, "
"your in-text\n"
"        citations are included in the word limit."
msgstr ""

#: templates/FAQ.html:141
msgid "Q. Is it necessary to include footnotes or endnotes in an essay?"
msgstr ""

#: templates/FAQ.html:142
msgid ""
"A. You <strong>may not</strong> include footnotes, but you may include "
"in-text citations\n"
"        or endnotes. You should give your sources of any factual claims "
"you make, and you should acknowledge any other\n"
"        authors on whom you rely."
msgstr ""

#: templates/FAQ.html:148
msgid ""
"Q. I am interested in a question that seems ambiguous. How should I "
"interpret it?"
msgstr ""

#: templates/FAQ.html:150
msgid ""
"A. You may interpret a question as you deem appropriate, clarifying your "
"interpretation if\n"
"        necessary. Having done so, you must answer the question as "
"directly as possible."
msgstr ""

